<p>Because the goalposts in Canadian football are on the goal line, and bec=
ause downing the ball in the end zone results in the kicking team scoring a=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_(Canadian_football)" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Single (Canadian football)">single point</a>, fie=
ld goal returns are much more common. The longest missed field goal return =
in the CFL is 131 total yards. Against the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Montreal_Alouettes" title=3D"Montreal Alouettes">Montreal Alouette=
s</a> on August 22, 1958, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toro=
nto_Argonauts" title=3D"Toronto Argonauts">Toronto Argonauts</a>' Boyd Cart=
er ran 15 yards, then threw a lateral to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Dave_Mann_(American_football)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Dave M=
ann (American football)">Dave Mann</a>, who then returned it for the final =
116 yards.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-38" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_goal#cite_note-38"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This return, which=
 started 21 yards behind the goal line, was during the era of 25-yard end z=
ones (which made the maximum theoretical missed field return distance 134 y=
ards in those days) and therefore cannot be met or exceeded on the modern f=
ield with 20-yard end zones. Since the shortening of the end zones in the C=
FL in 1986, a field goal has been returned for the maximum 129 yards on fou=
r occasions: by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bashir_Levingston"=
 title=3D"Bashir Levingston">Bashir Levingston</a> of the Toronto Argonauts=
 on June 28, 2007,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-39" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_goal#cite_note-39"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> by <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominique_Dorsey" title=3D"Dominique Dors=
ey">Dominique Dorsey</a> also of the Toronto Argonauts on August 2, 2007,<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-40" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Field_goal#cite_note-40"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>39<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> by <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Tristan_Jackson" title=3D"Tristan Jackson">Tristan Jackson</a=
> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saskatchewan_Roughriders"=
 title=3D"Saskatchewan Roughriders">Saskatchewan Roughriders</a> on July 14=
, 2012,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-41" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Field_goal#cite_note-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>40<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and by <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trent_Guy" title=3D"Trent Guy">Trent Guy</a> of =
the Montreal Alouettes on September 23, 2012.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_goal#cite_not=
e-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>41<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup>
</p>
